================================================================================
1. The command to create a new file (or update the timestamp on a file which already exists) is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  mkfile
	B.  create
	C.  touch
	D.  upfile

================================================================================
2. The command to display the current working directory is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  ecd
	B.  cd
	C.  cwd
	D.  pwd

================================================================================
3. A process is a program that is being executed by the operating system.
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  True
	B.  False

================================================================================
4. Redirection may be used to direct standard output to a file.
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  True
	B.  False

================================================================================
5. The command to list the contents of a directory is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  ld (lowercase "L", lowercase "D")
	B.  listdir
	C.  ls (lowercase "L", lowercase "S")
	D.  list

================================================================================
6. Which of the following commands will append text to an existing file?
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  echo "Hello, again!" > out.txt
	B.  echo "Hello, again!" >> out.txt
	C.  echo "Hello, again!" << out.txt
	D.  echo "Hello, again!" < out.txt

================================================================================
7. Paths which begin at the root are called relative paths.
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  True
	B.  False

================================================================================
8. Unix integrates all files into a single directory structure.
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  True
	B.  False

================================================================================
9. A file is either a destination or source for a stream of data.
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  True
	B.  False

================================================================================
10. The command to echo text to the screen is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  display
	B.  echo
	C.  print
	D.  write

================================================================================
11. The command to change to a new directory is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  cwd
	B.  cd
	C.  chdir
	D.  pwd

================================================================================
12. What command can be used to view a directory hierarchy?
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  ls
	B.  pwd
	C.  tree
	D.  shrb

================================================================================
13. What symbol is used to represent the user's home directory?
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  $ (a dollar sign)
	B.  \ ( a backslash)
	C.  ~ (a tilde)
	D.  / (a slash or forward slash)

================================================================================
14. The command used to create a new directory is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  createdir
	B.  cwd
	C.  mkdir
	D.  cd

================================================================================
15. The command to return to the previous directory after a command was issued to temporarily change the directory is:
------------------------------------------------------------
	A.  pushd
	B.  popd
	C.  pd
	D.  pwd
